,Recommended,237930,10929376,"Posted: 28 June, 2014",all,purity,"This game is fantastic. Beautiful art style, fun combat and gameplay, and boasts strong replay value (a rarity for me).  Instead of the weapon choices of Bastion, you have four separate slots in which you can make different and unique combinations of three different programs each, in addition to four passive slots.  The variety will keep you playing without a doubt. ""Dying"" removes one of your slots and the program within it until you reach a checkpoint, which forces you to experiment with new combinations if you aren't careful. Soundtrack is breathtaking and truly draws you into the game with the ""hummed"" overlay when you go into VATS / planning mode. Finally, it's all wrapped up with a cute love story featuring a Narrator™.Cons:- Mildly short, but the side content and the replay value does make up for it quite a bit.- UI is unintuitive and unfriendly (actually a rather large downside considering how much time you spent mixing and matching different programs), but can be navigated once you get used to it.Please buy this game it is sexy and awesome."
76561198011650742,Recommended,237930,22682711,"Posted: 27 April, 2016",all,HunterFX21,"As most steam players, I was caught up in my library.I would stare at my game list, as hours and hours passed, until I finally was inspired to do something ""else.""My first moments in Transistor were skeptacle. After so many hours staring at my game library, I couldn't believe that a game could offer me the satisfaction I was looking for.I thought this was an entirely tactics-based game - I was wong. This is an action packed game with a strategic function akin to fallout 3. The art style and level setup in this game is truly masterful.The combo system for ""functions"" is amazing. I love being able to combine my ""Switch()"" move with my ""Load()"" move. Each move (as an upgrade, passive, or active skill) has its own charm. The combinations are fun to explore and really add to the overall experience.""Limitors"" are a way to make the game harder (and more fun). By adding ""limitors"" you add to the enemy difficulty and experience bonus after each battle. It's really rewarding and fun.I don't know why I didn't play this game early.It's really a great game with a driving plotline and replayability."
