,Recommended,237930,10214269,"Posted: 23 May, 2014",all,Ladyy Yennefer,"Short, yet very sweet. Everything about this game is art, from the music to the graphics to the story.Transistor is a sci-fi action adventure game with a combat system that's a mix of hack & slash and turn-based. You get about 20 ""functions"" which can each be used in three roles: firstly as a combat skill, secondly as an upgrade for skills, and thirdly as a passive that effects all skills and combat. You can install and uninstall these functions as much as you like, giving you lots of flexibility. As you level up you also get the choice to use limiters, which buff your enemies. These are optional, so you can challenge yourself however you see fit.The only thing this game needs is more content. However, you can replay the game retaining all your skills and level from the previous playthrough, and there are special arenas that test your skill.Definitely worth checking out."
