,Recommended,237930,28905116,Posted: 1 January,all,[StSv] Neth,"Having just finished this, all I can really say is:Transistor is an experience, that everyone needs to try.The visuals are amazing.The soundtrack is beautiful.The gameplay is diverse, theres so many ways to suit it to your playstyle, as you can basically augment and change your attacks/abilities. Flitting around between styles was fun, albeit very challenging at times, as some enemies... are kind of unfair, at times.The story is left intentionally vauge mostly, but gives enough to leave a strong plot. The detatched storytelling used works well, and the ending is... something.The main appeal of the game has to be the story and the graphics, but yet theres still some replayability, as new game+ is a thing. On top of this, there are optional limiters to add challenge, if you so wish.The only potential weak points I can think of are:- Recharge from Turn() is very annoying, to be frank, as most of your abilities are offline. This can be partially removed by augmenting with an ability called Jaunt(), but its still a pain, especially in a very risky scenario.- The final boss is... frankly, underwhelming? It seemd rather gimmicked and just a spamfest, with no real difficulty. I dont know if thats because I found a combination able to completely demolish it, but still.Overall, Transistor is a downright gorgeous game that has to be at least tried at some point."
