,Recommended,237930,33511631,Posted: 13 July,all,Solvaij,"9/108 hoursI came across this game during a steam sale and decided to give it a shot. It was so worth it. The art design and soundtrack are just fantastic, and the aesthetic is enthralling. The transistor's ability to pause time allows for an elegant blend of tactical and hack-and-slash battles, and the endgame is simply awesome. My only complaint is that the story is not as well-defined as it could be. While it certainly succeeds in piquing interest in it's digital backdrop, it doesn't follow through with enough information to satisfy. The function logs help, though, and there is a fascinating story to be told. You just have to hunt for it. Overall, fantastic. I definitely recommend it to anyone who likes strategy games."
