,Not Recommended,237930,12177075,"Posted: 21 September, 2014",all,spooky,"I had high expectations because of Bastion. But i don't recommend it because of some points:* The narration. Bastion had an innovative narration and this game tries to copy that but in the end it just make random comments and it really distracts you from the game. ""Oh, i guess they don't like to swim"" as you pass by a pond. ""Let me tell you a joke.. What's the difference between... You know what? nevermind"" during a lift ride (loading screen disguised)* The Combat. It is nice in the beggining but gets repetitive really fast. you do get some powers but they mostly play out the same. You fully heal between fights and can save everywhere. If you die, you don't really die as the time stops and you lose one of your attacks until the second next checkpoint. I really wish it had more depth, but in the end it was  1- stop time 2- queue some attacks 3- run as your time stop ability recharges 4- repeat* The story. I am a little biased because i skipped all terminals. Or maybe i skipped them all because the reading doesnt really fit the action oriented gameplay. I didn't understand many points but in the end i didnt bother going after the information. I was just happy the game was ending. Also, I didn't care about the protagonist.* The protagonist. Female silent protagonist. you are supposed to feel her emotions through her music (why is she a singer anyway?) and like her because of her appearance (red haired, nice body, etc). But you don't. She is shallow. Lacks personality. She just does what the sword tells her to do. The ending went against what was being shown, though.* The length. It was quick. Surprisingly quick. When the final cutscene appeared i though I was just less than halfway though but it was actually the end. I was just level 11 and still had space for countless powers and upgrades. i didn't even unlock most restrictions.  What happened ?* The linearity. I guess if they went a route a little more like bastion it would have been better. many stages that you get a new power per stage, or something like that. But this game just makes you follow the path and that is it.I really loved the ending, though. But it doesn't make the game any betterI wish i liked it, but i really didn't."
