,Recommended,237930,11167724,"Posted: 10 July, 2014",all,Neo Way,"A spiritual successor to Bastion? Well, that's right, but it's not just that. This game has a whole lot of content to be explored, such as the backstory of Cloudbank, the reasons behind the Process starting their attacks on Goldwalk, how and why Red got the Transistor and what's the connection between her and the one inside the Transistor. The battle system couldn't be more impressive, as you must have a lot of vision on what will happen to decide your own actions in a turn, taking into account not only the reactions you cause with your actions, but the actions the enemy may take when you attack. One such example is the Younglady (no spoilers are given), which can be somewhat frustrating at first, but it still makes you want to keep trying untill you finally manage to break the pattern. This not to mention the huge amount of possibilities there are to use the Functions in many different ways, using them as Active, Passive or Upgrades. I was very satisfied with the story, gameplay, visual, soundtrack... The game as a whole is astonishing. I highly recommend giving it a try if you like RPGs, and even if you don't enjoy RPGs that much, you may change your mind with this game."
