,Recommended,237930,11703530,"Posted: 14 August, 2014",all,Busch,"It was initally the track ""Old Friends"" from the trailer that drew me in so it was very much a case of came for the music, stayed for the experience.Storyline is an inbetween lines tale of love admist revenge.Gameplay is a fusion of real time hack and slash similar to Bastion but at a slower pace with the ""Turn Mode"" being like a tactical mode similar to V.A.T.S via the recent Fallout games (3 and New Vegas). Overall gameplay is not complicated and encourages experimentation with rewarding results. Also there are options via ""Limiters"" to increase the difficulty and affect consequntly how you utilize many of the protagonist's abilites as you level up.  Battles can be long and enduring, but this is very much true to life itself.The music and art style is what gives this game it's atmosphere. The soundtrack is an eclectic fusion of dissonance and consonance with genres such as eletronica, rock,  downbeat, jazz and vocal. There are quite a few notable tracks that are awesome to listen to for pure audial pleasure. Art style is very reminiscent of the late 19th century styles with Art Nouveau, Henri de Toulouse-Lautrec and Gustav Klimt.Transistor is a wonderful game for its subtle poetic atmosphere and storyline that verges into the territory of Romanticism with Heinrich von Kleist.A beautiful game!"
