,Recommended,237930,11065570,"Posted: 4 July, 2014",all,nagN,"Transistor is quite possibly one of the best games to come out in the past 5 years.Everything about this game hits the sweet spot in a way I can only hope to convey in words, The world building is masterful and I would expect no less from the likes of Super Giant games being the master of the art. The gameplay is a mesh of Tactical RPG and an Action RPG, There being a way to switch between real time and the planning stage makes the game go as fast as you want it to go and tailors your combat choices accordingly. The story is somewhat the games weakpoint as it is somewhat vague but very open to interpretation so it will give you some food for thought. This game is worth £30, let alone £15 and should be a must play for people who are into masterful worlds and and rich gameplay. My only complaint would be that the game is a bit on the short side but that is fixed by new game plus letting you keeping all your upgrades and functions while starting from the beginning of the game again. Transistor is a enjoyable albeit short experience that I can recommend to anyone."
