,Recommended,237930,13057252,"Posted: 23 November, 2014",all,951Jimbo,"I give transistor ⅗ stars.I bought Transistor solely because it is from the same developer that made one of my favorite games, Bastion.  While Transistor is still a good game I was somewhat disappointed.The Good:-As of mid November 2014 I didn’t encounter ANY bugs or instability issues, a common complaint at launch-The graphics are good, but should still work on lower-end systems-The turn based gameplay is well done for the most part-Reasonable price for a game at 6 hours of play-Has some replayability to it-While not the best story, and a little confusing at times, I think the ending ties everything up nicely and makes you think a bit. Even though the story was lacking it kept me coming back for more to finish the game.The Bad:-The graphics, in my opinion, are not nearly as clever as Bastion.  Bastion used beautiful bright cell-shaded/watercolor style graphics to illustrate a strange and troubled world.  Transistor relies heavily on a beautiful but dark watercolor style that looks more sophisticated but is less enjoyable to look at for 6 hours of game.-The characters aren’t as likeable, developed, or funny, as Bastion’s.  The narrator of Bastion was one of the best features.  In this game the transistor character makes soft-pointless observations throughout the game that don’t add very much creative value-The turn style gameplay is again, in my opinion, a step back.  In Bastion I spent hours mastering the various weapons in the proving ground.  This game has a similar proving ground structure but the turn style combat feel easy and disconnected.  I imagine many gamers will  disagree with me on this point.-Music is a large element to the game and passing various tests unlocks more music.  However, I found the music itself to be pretty boring and uninteresting.  I have fairly broad taste in music so I imagine many will agree with me.  I’m glad I didn’t pay extra to get the boring soundtrack because I cannot imagine wanting to listen to it at any time.Based on these reasons, I give the game ⅗ stars.  Yes, it is fun, and it is well done; but it could be so much better.  I will likely follow this developer and buy future titles with the hope that they are a bit more fun than this one."
