76561198052904779,Recommended,237930,10408421,"Posted: 9 June, 2014",all,brendanbyron3,"Think of it as Diablo 2 with an optional turn-by-turn mode in a beautiful art deco apocalypse.To boil it down, you choose between 'functions' (which work like attacks in Pokemon: of many, you only get four at once) to mow down robots in a gorgeously-rendered future city.The kicker: every few seconds you can pause the action, move about, and queue up a combo of attacks. When you unpause, you whoosh about the battle spitting explosions. You've got a few seconds of helpless fleeing - then you're off again, chaining up attacks.Trust me: nothing beats laying down three consecutive damage multipliers on a high-level enemy then knocking them off in a single hit.Difficulty can be raised with optional handicaps called Limiters.There's a clever system around the functions themselves, too: any function can modify another or provide a passive bonus. I.e., you can add a quick-firing attack to a slower one – increasing the slower attack’s speed, but forgoing the quicker attack entirely."
