,Recommended,237930,10574315,"Posted: 20 June, 2014",all,Moose,"You played Bastion. You loved it and can't wait to play Transistor, but hold on. This game is not what you expect it to be. That doesn't mean its a bad game by any means, but this is a completely different experience from what you are expecting. Combat is mostly turn based and the game runs on rails for the most part. The game is also not fully fleshed out. Its obvious they ran out of ideas, time or money because the game doesn't quite set up the story as well as their previous one. You get character biographies from using skills but there is nothing more. The moments you do encounter other characters are brief and you will never get the answers you want about the setting. Where does this take place? What is the process? What were the Camerata's goals? The game teases at an explanation but stops short of actually filling in the blanks. Buy this game on sale and enjoy it for the brief distraction that it is. You will probably enjoy it."
