76561197971825130,Recommended,237930,10264385,"Posted: 28 May, 2014",all,Haapy,"I really like this game. The music is beautiful, as are the visuals. The voice acting is nice, tho there are some weird pauses between lines. I sometimes find myself waiting for the second half of a sentence that never comes, or thinking a line is done and then it continues a few seconds later. A little weird. But the quality is very high. And I love that sword guy's voice ;oPThe combat system is enjoyable. Lots and lots of options to play with. You have a number of skills that can be either used as a primary skill (like hit 'em with the sword, or shoot a bolt of energy at a distant foe), or they can be slotted into a different primary (like add damage, or AoE to some other skill), or they can be used to provide a more general buff (you have a damage shield, or all backstabs do more damage). That's really clever, and it is surprisingly intuitive to use. I'm a huge fan of the pause-time-and-queue-up-your-actions mechanic as well.I'd highly recommend it, if you're into RPGs."
