,Recommended,237930,10312723,"Posted: 1 June, 2014",all,Bigeloaf,"Transistor is made by SuperGiant Games, who are well known for their other masterpiece: Bastion. Both of these games have similarities with the isometric view, and feelings of being lonely. What Transistor does to break the mold and to step out from behind Bastion's shadow is amazing. It's sci-fi centric, and the musical selection of jazz is a great mood setter. Combat contrasts greatly from Bastion. In Bastion, the combat was fast-paced with very little cooldown and strategic plans. Transistor is all about the strategy standpoint as your attacks are slow as molasses, but brings in the mechanic of stopping time and planning attacks that will be automatically executed very fast after you set the plan. The artwork is beautiful and is very colorful. The levels are greatly detailed. The only voice heard during the game is the voice of the sword (i guess this will be a common theme among games by SuperGiant). If you are a fan of Bastion, this game is a must buy. If you didn't play Bastion and like games with strategic mechanics fused with some action, this is a perfect example.Transistor gets a 10/10 in my book."
