,Recommended,237930,13948521,"Posted: 11 January, 2015",all,Lysander,"Absolutely beautiful game.  The art, sound, and music are amazing.  The story is intriguing, though not as much is explained as I would like.  There are hints of deeper secrets in the game, but that is left to the imagination.The gameplay was odd at first, but once a few abilities are unlocked it becomes pretty good.  Each ability can serve three functions, which creates a lot of variety with many combos.  I liked the ""Turn"" system which makes the game more strategy oriented (especially compared to Bastion).  The game is pretty linear, consisting of progressing between arena-like areas, but the environments keep everything feeling new and fresh.I loved the writing.  Each ability comes with a character backstory that is unlocked by using each of the ability's functions.  Each time I got a new ability I quickly used each function just so I could read the fascinating backstories.Overall, this was a pretty good game.  I recommend it to anyone."
