,Recommended,237930,10290744,"Posted: 30 May, 2014",all,conninator,"I write this after experiencing five hours of pure excellence in game design.Transistor is an absolute beauty. I would go as far as calling it a work of art. The backgrounds and environments are lovely to look at. The music is at times upbeat, at times ambient, but always a joy to listen to. The vocals by Ashley Barrett make me just... melt. The story is told in an interesting way, and you feel like a part of it. I would recommend playing it alone for full immersion.The game's combat mechanics are complex yet simple, allowing two different playstyles. The game can be played like Bastion, with full real-time combat, or you can plan out your moves and execute them all at once using Turn(). (my personal preference.) Functions (the game's moves) can be swapped at any ""Access Point"" and can stack onto other Functions for greater effectiveness.I have extremely enjoyed my time with Transistor. Supergiant Games has hit another home run. Please, support this fine team of game developers and play this game. You will enjoy it very much. I know I have."
