,Recommended,237930,33384982,Posted: 8 July,all,Cap'n Potato,"9/10Great game.The graphics are great and it is pretty easy to run.The gameplay is somewhat repetitive, but you can very easily change your playstyle by picking different 'functions' (abilities). You are also forced to do this when you run out of health. The game doesn't have a difficulty setting, but you can choose your own difficulty while playing by using limiters. These make the fights harder by giving the enemy advantages. The more of these limiters you have enabled, the faster you level up.The story is pretty good, but it does require a lot of reading and swapping of playstyles to understand fully. (When you pick different functions, bits of the story are unlocked.)The soundtrack is absolutely amazing.Even though this game is quite short (I completed the story in 6 hours), you can still keep playing after you finish the story. You start at the beginning of the story again, but you will keep all of your unlocks and player level and fight stronger enemies."
