,Recommended,237930,10509771,"Posted: 17 June, 2014",all,Eph,"Beautifully executed game. Combines a 1920s theme and a future technology theme that blend together almost perfectly, and is can be seen throughout the game in the numerous splash artworks that are found as you go. The voice actor for the transistor, personally, has the mode captivating voice I have ever heard since Rucks from Bastion. The combat system in the game is well done, and the various abilities and combinations allow for different types of gameplay. It's somewhat of a real-time, yet turn-based method, where you can basically stop time to plan out your attacks. Once you have completed attacking, you must survive the next few seconds until you have a chance to stop time again. The storyline itself is understood as a love story from the beginning, with a tragic end. The music in the game is atmospheric and soothing, and the soft, muffled humming that can be heard in-between turns is possibly my favorite part of the game. I'm hope that they will release a Transistor announcer for Dota 2, because the Transistor's voice is sublime.10/10, would recommend to anyone."
