76561198075383350,Recommended,237930,24449033,"Posted: 21 July, 2016",all,All Hail Syndra,"Jesus Christ, I don't have words enough to describe how perfect this game is.First off: looks. 10/10The minute I looked at this game, I knew I'd want to play it. Attractive, attention-drawing female lead character who turned out to be amazingly pretty and humble. Then, the art. Oh my God. Flawless, perfect, awesome. Everything drawn to its smallest detail, and all very thought-through for the whole gaming experience. The mixture of lights in-combat makes you want to play it nonstop.Gameplay: 10/10At first, I was a little concerned about it being a 2D game (not because 2D games are bad, but because I tend not to like them). Actually, I saw it be launched back in 2014, but was not caught in the moment to buy it. Then, I decided to give it a shot now. Best idea so far. I couldn't find a single bug ingame, not to mention how fluid the animations are. But the best part: ingame sound experience. Sweet Lord. Best game I've ever played, by far. Games are not about graphics or long stories, but how much they can make you dive into the atmosphere and really feel you're the character. And boy, does this game excel at this. I truly felt I was a red-haired woman with a talking technologic-sword in a city where everything'd been consumed by programs. One point I really liked was the fact that whenever she hums, it goes according to whatever song is currently playing in the background. It really shows the commitment the team had in doing this game, and planning it so the story would feel real. I cared for Red and her sword, I did. I felt like a child rooting for them when the sword got red and it seemed it'd be corrupted away from her. Very immersive.Art/Music/Story: 9.9/10Exerything perfect. You can't find one single image that says 'look how poorly drawn I was'. None. Very hard work applied into creating this world and the story. Everything makes sense, there aren't loose ends. All songs were very good, highlight on ""In Circles"", which is a favorite and definetly could be a pop singer' single. Red's voice is something unique, I don't know wheter because the effects or what, which also don't mind. The fact is you get goosebumps and shivers everything she hums to a song. The reason my grade isn't 10 is the ending, which I'd hoped would be the other way around. But, I must not spread spoilers.All in All: 10/10I don't recommend it. I command people to play it. :)"
