76561198014856048,Recommended,237930,13732824,"Posted: 31 December, 2014",all,SunriseAtSunset,"This is a masterpiece.I've always loved games that tell the story through every single element of the gameplay, and Transistor is no exception. You can choose how much you learn about the characters involved in the story, which is told through the voice of the Transistor for the most part. The voice acting is superb and embellishes an already-compelling tale. The soundtrack--don't even get me started--the soundtrack is massively beautiful, adding to and improving upon the story and world of the game. The visuals are both vibrant and not distracting. And the ending...the ending is exceedingly well-done and satisfying to me as a gamer, and as someone who'd gotten invested in the characters.What really set this game apart for me was the combat system. I am usually a FPS gamer, so this was a new and intriguing experience. By customizing your chosen 'functions' you're also able to customize how you fight the enemies. In addition to that, the turn mode is REALLY interesting. It takes some getting used to, but the transition period is not overly long.All in all, Transistor has rocketed to a spot on my list of Top 5 games. This game is a work of art, simply put, a work of art to be appreciated and revisited. I only wish the base game were longer, but it felt perfectly timed."
