76561197999824868,Recommended,237930,17720061,"Posted: 25 August, 2015",all,Geodude07,"So I have a rough time figuring out how I feel about this game.But let me try.The combat, the music, the environment were all beautiful. The character design was striking and really I can't say how much I enjoy playing the game for what it is. I enjoy the narration to, which comes from your sword, though sometimes his commentary is pretty empty or generic. I feel a lot more could have been done there.My problem here is the story and the characters.A lot of this game is ambigious and parts of it are meant to be. However too much of it is. We don't know a lot of the things our characters would, concepts and ideas are brought up but we never get a decent explanation. I feel like knowing what the 'country' is would be nice. I mean it could be implied to be death, or it could be people logging out of the virtual world...which is confusing.Some text in game makes it sound like many people are dying, yet other commentary makes it seem like people might have just left. Afterall it seems the world is virtual...to some extent. It makes you wonder about how it all works. Yet this is never really explored. I get wanting things to be mysterious, but in thise case it feels like it would just be basic information. Maybe it's not too important though....Afterall this is a love story in the end, but I think things could have been done to make the player feel more satisified with the ending and more invested in the characters. While the story isn't terrible by any means, it feels like we could have seen a lot more interesting interactions, explored what this utopia was really like and made it all feel more meaningful.To me though...the game was fun, I did like the style and while the characters weren't all that fleshed out I did want to know about them and I did end up caring about what happened to the two main characters."
