,Recommended,237930,11400757,"Posted: 25 July, 2014",all,Owari-no-splee,"From Supergaint Games (the same people who brought you Bastion), comes he Sci-FI Acton RPG Transistor, a game that feels like a more futuristic Bastion but with a futuristic setting and with a silent female protagonist named Red, with the narrator taking the form of the talking sword she carries with her (that has he conciousness of a man close to Red) as she peices together what happened to her as well as what is happening to the city of Cloudbank. The game's soundtrack fits in perfectly and is really quite amazing. The game gives the player the job of trying to peice together the stpry as it unravels through voice recordings, terminal messages, and exchanges between the characters. The game can be played with a gamepad but i found a mouse and key to suit better for gameplay. The combat system is complex in the sense that Red has the ability to stop time with ()turn and allow her to plan movements, attacks and combos with limitations of course. Take too much damage and a function you have equipped will short circuit, casuing you to return to another user terminal to try and recover it after a battle. Having all your functions destroyed ultimately cuases death. Each function can be equpided to the Transistor for a main attack, another function for an added effect, or to Red herself for a buff like extended health. The fuction system provides different styles of gameplay and different powerful combinations. The versitility of how these functuions are equipped add to the story becuase the functions, appart from being attacks and various buffs, are actually the essenses of some of cloudbank's finest. The more you use a function in a different slot, the more you'll discover about the person behind the function. The game does a great job of haing the player peice together what is going on, tagged along with a great soundtrack, gorgeous graphics and snazzy voice work make a great game. BUT the game feels just a tad short...that's what made me a little disapointed..so while the game is good, it is recomended to buy during a sale :p"
