,Recommended,237930,10956064,"Posted: 29 June, 2014",all,snakepaws,"Do NOT expect a sequel to Bastion. This is not it.Now that that's out of the way, it's a solid enough game. Darren Korb, the composer from Bastion, is back with a fantastic soundtrack; just don't expect more ""frontier trip hop"" that you may be wanting. The narrator is also back, but less rustled.This game LOOKS like Bastion, but the fighting mecahnics are definitely different. Where Bastion was more hack n' slash, Transistor is almost turn-based. You stop time (think VAT system in Fallout 3), line up and target enemies with attacks, see what damage it'll do, undo, adjust, etc, and then release time and unleash hell. The system works well.Bottom line, it's a fantastic game - just don't expect it to be another Bastion."
