,Recommended,237930,20096565,"Posted: 29 December, 2015",all,Axe Raider,"GameOfTheYear()Absolute masterclass. This game is way ahead of its time. The story is engaging, the art style is beautiful, the level design is stellar, and the soundtrack is downright incredible.It's got some of the most interesting and thoughtful combat mechanics in any game I've ever played. There's a Fallout-esque VATS style system where you plan attacks and then execute them, so it plays like a pseudo turn-based action RPG. Chaining various combinations, abilities, and upgrades all make the player feel very intelligent and the payoff is not only extremely rewarding but is also intensely satisfying.It does not spoonfeed you how everything works and there's no handholding whatsoever. It leaves it all up to the player to figure it out. It's going for full immersion and it does it wonderfully. I'm telling you, the things this game tries are extremely ambitious and super eccentric, which a lot of game studios are afraid to do for fear of alienating their player base.I won't say any more. There's more quality, love, dedication, and sheer genius in this game than most triple-A titles. Supergiant Games is a studio that's clearly way more mature than their age suggests.Buy this, you won't regret it."
