76561197976864444,Recommended,237930,10224063,"Posted: 24 May, 2014",all,hat,"Transistor is just beautiful. The design, the art style. It's just second to none.Also, the soundtrack. It's a masterpiece.The game mechanics, including fights, are far better and improved comparing to Bastion. They are easy to master, very nice to handle on both 360 Pad and mouse+keyboard. No problem there at all everything is great. The turn-based and real-time combat mix works PERFECT. I was afraid of this before the release but it turned out to be just amazingly done making you want to use both and blend them together.Skill/Functions/Character development is innovative and give you a lot, and I mean A LOT of different possible builds and the game itself/story development does a great job on encouraging you to switch your tactics as often as you can.Although. After finishing I think, that I liked Bastion a little bit better. Probably because it was first and it was a surprise. The only thing I'd like Transistor to have is a bit more lore given to you by the narrator. Not through the people's description which you can find, but through the sword itself. Like Bastion did it.If you haven't played Bastion and you're thinking about getting Transistor: Play Bastion first.If you played Bastion and you're thinking about getting Transistor: Please, by all means.If you do not like how the game looks, or you are not into the SciFi or anything: Well, if you read it - try it. Sometimes we appreciate something that we do not necessarily like at first sight.Took me ~8 hours to complete. I was taking my time though, reading everything I could find.Game as close to perfection as this happens very rarely. Do not think, buy and play!9+/10. Along with Bastion and both Portals on the top of my All Time Masterpieces list."
