,Recommended,237930,10383557,"Posted: 7 June, 2014",all,Scary Monster,"Transistor is a rare game that combines sleek, smart combat, an incredible soundtrack, gorgeous level design, interesting gameplay, a captivating story with great pacing, and some of the best voice acting I've ever heard in a game to become something so much more than its individual parts. The functions, upgrades, passives and limiters work together seamlessly, and Transistor trusts that you're capable of figuring out the best combinations on your own. It's just intuitive enough without being condescending like many games recently.For me, the story is what really shone. The writing is consistently fantastic and draws you in right from the beginning of the game. I really felt like I was watching the destruction of a city I used to live in. I experienced a wide range of emotions from hope to anger to a huge sense of loss. The ending caught me off-guard; it's tragic, beautiful and heart-wrenching. It's not a terribly long game (~9 hours before NG+) but that doesn't matter. It's exactly as long as it needs to be.tl;dr buy Transistor it's really good"
