,Recommended,237930,24357034,"Posted: 16 July, 2016",all,KaZumaTree,"A sublime masterpeice done in the same vein as Supergiant Game's Bastion, with a well-designed hybrid real-time and turn-based combat system that shows they are willing to mix it up if it makes for a better game.+A beautifully directed sci-fi cyber-reality universe wherein the rules of the game's reality are bent or broken by the events transpired, rendered beautifully at every level+A unique real-time with pause-turns combat and progression system that fits the world as well as allow for vastly different approaches and playstyles.+Supergiant Games' famous narrated storytelling in strong form, combined with a compelling storyline and an equally compelling (if mute) main character.+Legendary musical direction that becomes an essential leg that the game stands on, and is hauntingly beautiful on its own.================-World and art direction can be somewhat esoteric and abstract for those unfamiliar with computer-based lingo, memes, and concepts.-Combat and progression system can be difficult to understand at the start.-Whilst the narrated storytelling device is solidly delivered (as well as the compelling story itself), it is a somewhat expected and somewhat overused mechanic at times.-Some minor inconsistencies in minor details for the universe (as well as lackluster sound effects) are noticeable."
