,Recommended,237930,16565212,"Posted: 20 June, 2015",all,tiny sushi,"This game is absolutely beautiful. Although I haven't had the chance to play Bastion, it's clear that the art director and artists from Supergiant games put a lot of hardwork and thoughtfulness into their character designs and game world. The music and soundtrack is also one of my favorite things about this game, with some of the songs mixing beautiful vocals and instruments with synth-techno that really added to the environment and even certain characters (I won't spoil who though).The combat style is definately odd, and if you're the type of person that prefers RTS games then you'll probably feel more at home than I was when I first started. Yes, it's a little hard to get used to, but at the same time the interesting variety and effects the game abilities have allow you to kind of ""mix and match"" your favorite ones to your keyboard/gamepad buttons, so in a way you're allowed to tailor your abilities to your playstyle. Eventually, after unlocking most of the abilities, I had gotten really used to the RTS style gameplay.Story-wise, this game is quite vague at times. There's more emphasis on trying to piece together what happened to the main character from the beginning and the little things like function files and dialogue between the main character and the sword can tell you a lot about what's happening. It's certainly quite linear and does try to make it open through the artwork and character dialogue/function files, but I get a sense that we've only got a small grasp on what this world's big picture is, which is somewhat disappointing considering how interesting the characters seemed to make it and how beautiful it's depicted.Unfortunately, this game is short. I was able to complete it within about 6 hours (and that says a lot considering how slow I am about completing games), and the boss battle at the end is.....underwhelming. It kind of just felt like I was fighting any other big tough brute monster from the game with a crapton of health tacked on.Nonetheless though, this is still an excellent game to play with interesting characters in a breathtaking science-fiction type world. I'd definately suggest it to anyone willing to try it."
