,Recommended,237930,15009204,"Posted: 22 March, 2015",all,Bear,"Another gorgeous, fun and thoughtful game. The game definitely feels like Bastion, with the story unfolding around you, but the new mechanics mean combat is less reactionary and more thoughtful, while remaining intense.The graphics and sound are coordinated beautifully, with Supergiant's signature narrative commentary and environmental touches. Like in Bastion, you pick from your powers, buffs, and challenges. However, the system is more flexible, allowing you to use any ability either as a primary power, a modifier for another power, or as a passive ability. This lets you experiment with power combinations and find a setup that's fun and effective. To prevent it from getting stale, the unlockable background information encourages (but doesn't force) you to keep mixing it up.While I do keep drawing comparisons to Bastion, this game very much stands for istelf as a distinctive, worthwhile experience."
