,Recommended,237930,10896394,"Posted: 27 June, 2014",all,DeadlyGhost,"Transistor is a truly different game, and that is what makes it so special. The graphical style is similar to Bastion, and the gameplay seems to be similar at first, but actually has much more strategy to it. As Red, weilding the Transistor, you have the ability to perform many uniqe and powerful abilities. At first, all you can really do is use those skills to attack the enemies in real-time, but shortly after the game begins you gain the ability known as Turn(). Turn () allows Red to slow down time and plan her attacks, which allows for very intense, strategic battles, rather than just attacking blindly. Another great aspect of Transistor is the music. I usually do not tend to care to much about a game's soundtrack, let alone end up buying it. The music is an awesome mix of jazz and techno. It is really stellar music that perfectly complements the game. Overall, Transistor is a truly unique game, the likes of which have never been seen before. If you are looking for a game with an interesting setting, amazing soundtrack, and strategic combat, then Transistor is the game for you."
