76561198085845512,Recommended,237930,32469086,Posted: 16 June,all,DeadEyeMaster1,"Indie games are going to dominate the market, they are the future of the video game industry.Certainly, the present indie games are founding the new genres for the future gaming reality.Transistor is going to be one of them. It focuses heavily on art style and combat design, utilizes as much resoureces as they can to output the maximized artistic style of a game. Artifying a game.We always know that game is a combination of art and entertainment, such a game heaviliy focusing on art makes it stand out among all other indie games. Even today, we hardly find this kind of refreshing game based off the limited resources they have had.The combat system is well-crafted to be diversified and fun, you can combine multiple perks into one action, and that one attack action would provoke the perks' effects out. Different perks different combinations, it's very cool to see it. And the system uses a real time engage clock, which is a pause in combat that allows you to draw out a tactic route to attack enemies. Something like the tactical view of Dragon Age, but rather the real time engage clock makes it kind of turn based.With this, we also have a niche story, even the story is kind of cliche but I really appreciate the voice acting of the characters in this game. The man in the sword's voice is just too good to be true. Story itself is interesting not yet engaging enough. But for the love of the arts in this game, you might as well appreciate that rather than the plot.Overall, 7/10."
,Recommended,237930,10184552,"Posted: 20 May, 2014",all,Tsuken,"Definitely what you'd expect from Supergiant. This game is a lovely little vaunt through their most recent aesthetic. You can expect much of what you got from Bastion, and if you've never played Bastion (how dare you), that simply means that you're getting your money's worth.The artistic sides of the game are, much like Bastion, its strongest points. The game is absolutely gorgeous, the voice acting is fantastic, and the music is beautiful as well. The gameplay itself could do with a bit of polish, but the combat and customization  systems themselves are innovative, enjoyable and deep.  Encounters will challenge and press you to synergize abilities, and the turn-based strategy elements that have been added to a Diablo-esque combat system give it a tactical depth that it wouldn't have otherwise, turning the game from frantic hack-and-slash to tactical nightmare in the blink of an eye.All in all, very well done, Supergiant! 9/10, with only one point deducted for a slight lack of polish on the gameplay front, as well as the fact that the game is a bit on the short side."
,Recommended,237930,10184892,"Posted: 20 May, 2014",all,A Classy Gentleman,"Another fantastic piece of work by Supergiant, the spiritual sucessor to Bastion does its predecessor justice. While the story is slightly more simple than the story in Bastion, the art direction, sound, music, and gameplay are all just as good, if not better. The game's core mechanic is the turn() function (ability) that you posess. Turn() allows you to freeze time and plan out your next move. It may not be the most original mechanic, but it works very well in this game.In addition, each of your attacks and abilities (called functions) can be used either as a primary attack, an upgrade to a primary attack, or a passive boost. For example, one ability, bounce(), when used as a main attack, fires a shot that ricochets between enemies. However, when applied as a boost to another ability, it causes that attack to have a possibility of ricocheting between enemies. Or it might reduce that attack's cooldown time, depending on the attack. Of course, it can also be used as a passive bonus, in this case granting the player a regenerating shield that reflects a single shot. As you can immagine, the number of possible combinations is enormous.Also, do yourself a quick favor. See the button that says ""Transistor + soundtrack""? Yeah? Good. Click that one. Because this game has some incredible music. I mean, the main character is a singer. It's like Darren Korb is rubbing how amazing of a composer he is in our faces. Don't believe me?http://supergiantgames.bandcamp.com.And that's not even touching on how beautiful this game is.This game will not disappoint you."
