76561198127276425,Recommended,237930,16990385,"Posted: 11 July, 2015",all,HardAppleCider,"Transistor is a wonderful game.It's very similar to Bastion in its design, but this isn't a bad thing.  The world setting here is a little bit more fleshed out and a little more my style.  Both games feature post apocalyptic worlds, but this one's all techie futuristic, and I dig that.If you've played Bastion you'll know what to expect.  The game's art style and simple (but fun) combat will make you want to keep playing until it's all over.  The game's on the short side, but that's why it's price is low.  It's a short sweet experience that I'd recommend to most people."
,Recommended,237930,10372766,"Posted: 6 June, 2014",all,Alex of Swag,Amazing
