,Recommended,237930,10687785,"Posted: 22 June, 2014",all,purebone00,"After beating the game on recursion mode (NG+), and obtaining all achievements. I have to say it's easily one of the most enjoyable games i've played. The combat is open and fun to experiment with, every function and skill seems to have it's purpose and makes for very interesting and different combat if you seek variety. With essentially 2 basic ways of playing turn() base, or playing in real-time. People will find what they feel comfortable with. The artwork and characters are simply amazing.There are some things about the game that should be noted.1.   it's short, having only taken me 16 hours to 100% it's very short compared to other games. Which actually has it's own pros and cons- prosthe story doesn't drag on and the setting and story is very well polished- consyou kinda wish it was longerin the end i loved the story and the characters, but i wish there was a little bit more.2.   it's not that difficult-  obviously it has a learning curve and once you get past that you can complete each of the challenges very fast,                 especially if you know what skills and combinations to use that are effective. (for example: there are these dog type enemies that are basically the biggest pain in the♥♥♥♥♥ but once you realise you can chain stun them or be able to evade them with the right timing and burst them down they become like little chiwawa's)- it's not as difficult as bastion was even accounting for the 10 gods/10 limitors gamemode. The 10 limitors add alot of difficulty to the game but there are some builds that are a catch all situation and you find yourself just plowing through enemies if you do search or create these builds.Final comment: I very much recommend this game, and makes me can't wait from what supergiantgames is going to release next. And if you do plan and buying and playing this game. Try and go into the game blind. Avoid as many spoilers and gameplay and even the enemy types (i realise i spoiled the dog, forgive me for that). Experience everything for yourself."
