,Recommended,237930,10274724,"Posted: 29 May, 2014",all,4RM3D [anime247],"If you like Bastion, you'll probably like Transistor also. It has the same atmosphere, but it has traded the fantasy-look for a more sci-fi-look. Another difference is the gameplay, which is quite unique and fun to play around with.WarningOne thing kinda annoyed me and that is the auto-save. You only have 1 save slot (excluding profiles) and no manual save. When entering a new area the game automatically saves. This can mess up your game severely. For example, I suddenly got into a boss fight, but I hadn't equipped all my skills properly as I was still experimenting. However you are stuck at the boss fight with no way to ""respec"" your skills or to reload the game to an earlier point.Also, if you want to explore everything, things could get nasty when you actually take the right path and the door slams shut behind you, with no way to explore the other paths.My advice is to regularly backup your save data in your Steam userdata folder."
