,Recommended,237930,18272456,"Posted: 30 September, 2015",all,ToadyBogard,"Lemme just give you a small rundown of pros and cons:Pros:+Beautiful soundtrack+Scenery just as beautiful+Can increase difficulty with 'limiters'.+Great plotCons:-A bit repetitive.-Enemies are repetitive.-Plot is a bit shallow if you don't pay attention to it.- It's kind of short.I'll admit, the first time I played this game I was confused and didn't know how to do things ingame, but then you learn how to and you're blazing through like a champ. Once you learn how certain enemies work and their various abilities, it's not hard to scamper to safety. (Jaunt will save your life more than once, I will tell you that much.)Plot is a bit shallow, sure. But honestly? It's not that shallow if you look more into it. It's basically about a group called the Camerata, their main goal is to keep control over the city of Cloudbank. They create pretty much a brush to make Cloudbank their canvas, the Transistor. With it, they begin taking out various people and testing out it's capabilities. One of their targets, a singer named Red was to be attacked but an unnamed person (Which, we can assume was Red's lover if you watch the credits roll.) defends her and is transferred into the Transistor himself. Now the two must stop the Camerata and the Process from destroying Cloudbank.I'll admit, the game is not everyone's cup of tea or whatever beverage you might like. No problems here, but please give this game a chance. Supergiant deserves so much praise for their great work and future endeavors."
