,Not Recommended,237930,13247061,"Posted: 5 December, 2014",all,boshanks,"As a big fan of Bastion I was really excited to play this game. I wanted to like it and I did like parts of Transistor. I 100% completed the game. This game has some interesting battle mechanics. The slot combinations are interesting to try out and let's you develop your own play style. And the game looks great and has a good soundtrack. (maybe I was spoiled with how great the Bastion soundtrack was that my expections were really high).Those are a lot of nice things but why the no recommendation? That said, this is a story-driven game. You follow a path, and like Bastion, you the player are thrown into a world starting to fall apart and you have to piece together. I don't want to spoil this for anyone, but I couldn't get invested in the story. This is a story game but even that you can get through.BUT I would not recommend this to anyone because of the save issues. Sane people would more or less uninstall after the first time you lose a game save or the game refuses to save at an access point or new area. I was so happy I finished the Risk() achievment just after the Spine fight because the game wouldn't save past that. And that was after this had happened several other times. This means on separate times I either played for a few hours, stopped at an access point (assuming I would have the game save) only to lose all of that progress. Or I had to keep playing until an access point registered a save. Not knowing if this basic feature you have no control over is going to not work completely took me out of the game and I slogged through it to 100% it. Don't do that to yourself. It's not worth the money or time. Oh and a 'patched' hardware crash happened to me as well.TL;DR: Looks great, sounds good. Story is...interesting. The save issues will ruin any positive experience you could have playing this game."
