76561197963213304,Not Recommended,237930,11518828,"Posted: 2 August, 2014",all,Tundraking,"Man, I really didn't think it would be hard for this game to please me. So that sword looking thing you see the main character with, is more of a wand, bummer, I like swords. The combat offers so many cool unique things to play with, sadly it is also slow, clunky, and thoroughly unsatisfying. The games flavor is largely rooted in refernces to programming language. You collect Functions as you progress and by using them directly, or to modify other functions you assemble your pool of attacks. This sounds great, and it is. However the animations are so slow, conversely enemy attacks are lightning fast. The pace of a battle is basically using a quick attack while you position yourself to use the ""Turn()"" system. This system freezes time and lets you queue up actions. This is where your slower more devastating attacks become usable. Most of the strategy comes down to bringing the moves that will maximize your potency in Turn() while having a plan to survive while you wait for Turn() to recharge.Sometimes you will find yourself dying almost instantly, many deaths feel cheap, and a few encounters I just rammed my face into a few times before just quickly winning it. **Before you waste your time with your L2P sentiments, let me inturrupt you. That is not a defense of poor game design** Of course one can get good at any game, but if that journey is unsatisfying one won't be very motivated to do so. This game would have been better off fully turn based as it's real time elements are unpolished.The art is beatiful, the voice acting convincing, and the overall flavor of the world is enough to draw you in initially. However, like many of the more notable story driven indie games, this one has the typical vagueness you've come to expect. While this vagueness is a great way to dive into the story at first, sticking to it through the end doesn't leave the audience smitten with curiousity, it just reveals a world with little to say.I can't recommend this game at full price, but if you want to play something a little different than your endless stream of shooters and mmos, and free to play nonsense this will satisfy an evening, though it will frustrate you with it's puzzling combat design choices."
