76561198027994280,Not Recommended,237930,16765337,"Posted: 28 June, 2015",all,Ismaru,"This game looks pretty awesome with it's appealing visual style, but furthermore I didn't like this game all too much.ProsLooks pretty goodYou can combine skills with eachother, allowing a lot of various approaches to each fightConsShort story - I completed the game in about 5-6 hours, the second replay was a lot shorter.Didn't like how the game punishes you for failing - you lose skills as you get closer to death, making the encounter even harder to beat, ending up in a vicious circle.It's really just walking from screen to screen, fighting your way through. I expected more puzzlesThe transistor blade would be awesome to insert into slots for various purposes (for example inserting it in a wall to use it as a lever for puzzles or something). Instead, it's really just a sword. It served no other gameplay function than that.There are ""limiters"" which are switches that make your game harder. That's great, if they weren't so mean-spirited and the reward for using limiters is too small. Sure, you could try another playthrough and make it more challenging, but the game doesn't really have anything new to offer in a replay. So why bother?Storytelling was very vague, the antagonist says weird stuff (during story moments it'd just go,""Hey, I got this funny joke I can tell you...""completely breaking the atmosphere the game is trying so hard to create.Asides from the musical tunes which are supported by the main characters humming, the audio quality wasn't very high. Looks like all the budget went into Red's voices and theme music.Was this review useful to you?Please check out the Izzy Reviews Curator pagefor regular updates on reviews for other games!"
