76561198070421597,Not Recommended,237930,20390366,"Posted: 7 January, 2016",all,NG14916,"I bought Transistor because people recommended it for having a good story. The gameplay is a somewhat fun fusion between strategy and action RPG, albeit very repetitive since the enemy types aren't mixed up that much - in the final area you almost exclusively fight a single enemy type in every battle which gets tedious.However, the story isn't very good. The ending is interesting, but the rest is lacking. Half the plot is buried in logs that you have to unlock by using your abilities in different ways. The logs are very dry and not particularly interesting to read. If they'd been spiced up, like by having them take the form of diary entries, they might allow some character development. Unfortunately, they read like encyclopedia entries.The other half of the plot is okay, but I couldn't bring myself to care very much about the city, the process, or the Camerata. Unfortunately the story doesn't do much to make you invested in what happens to the city since it's a pretty empty setting and you don't see it before the process starts attacking it. You also don't get to interact with many characters in the city, which doesn't help.The plot also just doesn't have much meat to it, with few twists and not much happening. That's not so bad since it's a fairly short game, but I would have liked to see a bit more. It has a good sense of atmosphere and the style of the dialogue has a noire feel. As a backdrop to the gameplay the plot is fine, but it doesn't stand well on its own.As far as characters go, the man in the sword is fairly interesting and you get pretty attached to him through the course of the story. Unfortunately, he's the only interesting character in the game. Red, the protagonist, had potential, but is unfortunately silent. She does occasionally communicate with the man in the sword through writing in terminals, but those moments are few and far between and don't convey an interesting personality. You get hints at an interesting relationship between Red and the man in the sword, but since she's silent it can't develop very much.Overall, I felt pretty disappointed by the story. But if all you're looking for is fun gameplay then this game might entertain you for a few hours."
