76561198003066842,Not Recommended,237930,17954334,"Posted: 9 September, 2015",all,SuperSpesh,"System requriments are a lie.Can you handle a top down game with mostly 2D visuals that avarage at 27 fps?! NO then dont but this. Also graphic settings are really poor . wont even allow me to change it to 720p from 1080p to fit the screen properly and boost up the fps.  Game it self is good but only if you have a decent computer. Bastion ran 2x better performance vise but combat and art style wasnt nearly as interesting.I found this fix to boost the fps 4 or 5 frames, But still low for my case.1. Right Click Transistor in your Steam Library2. Properties -> Set Launch Options...3. /Bloom=false /DrawRecursivePaths=false4. Hit ok and try running the game - see if that helpAdditionally you can set the following launch options, which may help with performance:/windowed /noborderYou may also increase performance by decreasing your resolution in-game."
