,Not Recommended,237930,24014379,"Posted: 2 July, 2016",all,Finraziel,"I don't like this game, and I'm not sure why apparently 96% of reviews are positive... The graphics are nice and the music is awesome, but the gameplay??? To me it falls completely flat on its face.There is a turn mechanic where you can pause the action and queue up some commands that Red (the protagonist) then executes very fast. After the turn however, you're left pretty much powerless and have to wait until you're able to do anything besides walking. Maybe this is supposed to invoke strategic play? To me it just seems dumb and I tend to ignore turn.But when not using turn, the game plays like a confusing arpg where you walk like through water and it's almost impossible to dodge. There is a power that lets you blitz in a direction, but it only slightly alleviates the problem. Most of your other attacks are also slow to use (with a buildup time) and once started you can't interrupt them, so no blitzing out.Then there's the fact that it's hard to get used to where your powers are. You're free to arrange them at certain points where you can customize your powers, but then there are special stages where you get powers assigned to you (and can't change the buttons) and the absolute worst thing that this game does: it strips powers from you when you die! (or rather, you don't die, you just lose a power). So if you were already struggling, now you're made weaker and if you rearrange your powers to compensate have to get used to a new control scheme again.All in all, the game just really confuses and frustrates me. Maybe if I'd persevere I'd get used to it, but seeing how many hours other reviewers put in before singing this game's praises, it's more likely that the game just isn't for me and I'm refunding it before passing the 2 hour mark.I personally don't recommend the game based on my experience, but since so many people do love it, I'd suggest you do try it and simply refund it if your experience turns out to be like mine. Oh and I did love Bastion..."
