,Recommended,237930,10571723,"Posted: 20 June, 2014",all,Angelore,"TL;DR: Transistor is good, you should pick it up if you liked Bastion or, in other words, if you like challenging combat and interesting storyline.That being said, what is transistor? It's an action-rpg game, where you have only one weapon, but it is very flexible and customizable. Leveling also affects weapon, there is no ""character skills"" whatsoever. The mechanics is unusual, it's a mix of time based and real time combat. At first I was sceptical about this, thinking that one of the modes will be way better, but that's not the case. Both modes are good, you can use one, other, or mix or them depending on your playstyle.The ""default"" combat is not very hard, as it was obviously designed for those who want to just see the story. But we are speaking of SGG, so they added a mechanics very similar to Bastion's Idols - Limiters, which can be activated/deactiated at any time, and will affect the strength, numbers and AI of enemies.The story is good, there is not much to say about it, the only downside being its length. This is arguably a downside, however, because the game doesn't feel too boring, and overextended.Also, the famous narrator is here, so this is definitely a big yay, imo."
