76561198039470520,Recommended,237930,10310646,"Posted: 1 June, 2014",all,Inquisitor Augen,"I was expecting Bastion, with a cyberpunk overlay and some gameplay tweaks.  I would have been delighted with that.  The combination of the Supergiant Games visual style with Darren Korb's music will get me every time, by itself.I found out in the first five minutes that this wasn't Bastion.  I was upset.  The controls felt clunky, not like the action I was used to.  The responses felt slow.  But the story gave me as much in the first five minutes as Bastion did, and that was enough.  I decided to stick it out, because the music got me, and the story, and the visuals.And I am so glad I did.Gameplay-wise, Transistor is actually not an action game as much as it is a uniquely-styled strategy game.  I thought the Turn() function was a gimmick, a ""bullet time"" for tight moments, but it's actually the way to play the game, to make it flow.  I had a moment, ten minutes in when I realized this, and that's when everything clicked together.I'm taking a break to write this review.  I haven't finished my first playthrough yet.  I'm looking forward to the reveals that I know are coming.  The twists have been straightforward, yes, but well-executed, and I'll take a wonderfully done formulaic story over a bumbled unique one, sometimes.This has been a wonderful game experience so far.  Supergiant, I'm along for the long haul with you guys.  Just keep bringing Darren Korb along for the ride, okay?  His music just completes everything.  Thanks for integrating the music, visuals, and story so well.Now if you'll excuse me, I have a game to finish."
