,Recommended,237930,10299454,"Posted: 31 May, 2014",all,The Goddamn Batman,"Short but enjoyable game. Pretty much everything you love about Bastion is here: great storytelling, music, and art style. The combat is an interesting combination of real time and turn-based with a fair amount of variety. Each new ability you get can be equipped as either an active attack, a modifier to another attack, or a passive ability. The game provides a practice room where you can try out whatever combination of abilities you like before using it in the real game. All in all, I found it to be a fun experience. Fair warning, though: when I say ""short"" I mean extremely short. About 5-6 hours is more than enough to go through the game and, other than 1 more playthrough on the new game+, there's not much replay value."
