,Recommended,237930,10263239,"Posted: 28 May, 2014",all,sneg_,"Great game! The narrative seems similar to Bastion but I prefer Transistor's storyline and style - sort of funky minimalist sci-fi world. The combat is cool, all abilities seem useful and there are a lot of different combos to explore.While in Bastion combat mechanic was more like a classic action/rpg hack-n-slash, Transistor is more turn-based - you have a ""planning mode"" where you can decide on the next course of action. Planning mode has a cooldown timer, so once you finish planning and all your actions are executed, you have to act in real-time until planning mode is available again. The game becomes more tactical but the cooldown on planning mode makes sure you do not abuse it, and helps to keep the game at a fast, challenging pace. When you run out of health, instead of seeing the typical ""game over"" screen straight away, your character loses one of her abilities. In my opinion, this is a very cool approach making the game less frustrating but equally challenging, as you have to master different abilities.Oh yes, and the soundtrack is great!If you like stylish games with fun gameplay and interesting storyline - do not miss this!!"
