76561198041742279,Recommended,237930,10487634,"Posted: 15 June, 2014",all,blogman100,"Many people will go into this game thinking it is Bastion..... THIS GAME IS NOT BASTION i repeat THIS GAME IS NOT BASTION. Its overall game feel and gameplay and very different and if you liked bastion you may not like this game.tl;dr: you and a talking sword go on an adenture.Not tl;drNow since that is out of the way, Transistor is an action rpg in an asemetric perpective that follows the story of Red in the city of Cloudbank. This game has an extroadinary soundtrack composed by the one and only Daren Korb and has a very interesting take on its gameplay. There are two ways to aproach combat, one way is to approach enemies in real time, and the other is during the ""turn"" mode. In this turn mode it freezes time and you can strategically move and perform attacks which will each diminish a portion of your energy bar. Many times i would find myself just waiting for my ""turn"" to recharge and then atack but others may prefer the real time combat opposed to the ""turn"" combat.Next, the astetic of the game is beutiful. With most of the assets hand drawn it brings to light a unique world with tons of character that definitaly stands apart from other games. Also, the characters are very interesting and the plot does not seem cookie cutter or monotinous.However the game does still have some problems. For example, some attacks do feel very overpowered and some players may find themselfs only using a specific itemset and not exploring other oppurtunities.In the end, the conjunction of the different ways and lore you recieve from abilities, visually appealing world, and fun combat i reccomend you give this game a try."
