,Recommended,237930,10194210,"Posted: 21 May, 2014",all,mH.NEGATiVE,"They had my money as soon as I played through Bastion the first time.    But with this game, while they revisit similar ground story and playstyle-wise.... Takes it up several notches.   The way you combine skills in-game makes for a VERY interesting way to play the game your own way.   For the first few levels you can play it like a hack and slash similar to Bastion, but once you get into it a bit, failing to use the innovative Turn mode will spell disaster for even minor enemy encounters.   This game brings ALL elements to bear in an absolute masterpiece... and it's yours for $20.   I spend that on coffee in a week.... OK... I spend WAY more than that on my caffeine habit... so what are you waiting for ?  More art from Jen Zee, more music from Darren Korb and Ashley Barrett... why are you still here reading this?!? GO GIVE THEM YOUR MONEY!TLDR: SUCH GAME.  MANY ART.  WOW."
